CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 4, 1952, pg. 22 reads: " "Big Break Of 1953" Winners - With W.C.Handy, famous composer of the "St. Louis Blues," as guest of honor, and Earsley Kincaid and Catherine Maddox as producers, the Greater Pittsburgh Improvement League announced the winners of their "Big Break of 1953" contest at Schenley High School last Friday night. The show announced prizes in several classifications.  First place winners are shown in photo on the left. They are, left to right: Anne Robinson, religious classification; Leon Daniels, popular; Louise Johnson, blues and Robert Mosely, light classics...- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: First place prize winners in the "Big Break Of 1953" music contest, from left: Anne Robinson, Leon Daniels, Louise Johnson, and Robert Mosely or Mosley, posed against curtain in Schenley High School
